<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 70 Kilograms of Heroin Seized in Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, June 21 (Xinhua) -- Turkish police seized 70 kilograms
of heroin in an operation against drug trafficking in western
Turkey, the semi-official Anatolia News Agency reported on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The agency said that the police, acting on a tip off, stopped
a caravan at Cesme Port in western province of Izmir and found the
heroin in secret parts of the vehicle.
</P>
<P>
The police took into custody four people including two Germans
in connection with the drug worth about 8 million U.S. dollars
on the international market, said the agency.
</P>
<P>
Turkey is on a transit route of drugs to Europe from the border
areas of Afghanistan and Pakistan. In 1996, Turkish police seized
4.4 tonnes of heroin, which accounted for 40 percent of the
world's total haul. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
