<DOCNO> XIE19980622.0010 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Batistuta Hat-Trick Highlights World Cup Finals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
PARIS, June 21 (Xinhua) -- Argentine star striker Gabriel
Batistuta highlighted the World Cup finals with the first hat-trick
so far in the match against Jamaica here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
On the FIFA "Fairplay Day", the Argentine team dominated the
match and nearly opened the scoring in the first minute when
Batistuta's shot was just wide.
</P>
<P>
But they didn't find the net until the 32nd minute when Ortega
completed a quick counter-attack with a volley shot.
</P>
<P>
The Aegentine team played better and more aggressive in the
second half. Ortega made it 2-0 for Argentine at the 55th minute.
</P>
<P>
It was at the 73nd minute when Batistuta began his splendid
performance. He launched two fierce shots at the goal at the 73rd
and 79th minutes respectively and get awarded with a goal each.
</P>
<P>
The Argentine team seemed not contented with the four-goal lead and
kept on launching attacks. Ortega was tackled down in the area at the
83rd minute and Batistuta converted the shot to complete his
hat-trick.
</P>
<P>
The 5-0 victory put both Argentina and Croatia into the round of
16 while Japan and Jamaica, the other two teams in Group H, are both
out of the contention. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
