<DOCNO> XIE19980622.0014 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Austrian Coach Says No Problem with Confidence </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BORDEAUX, France, June 21 (Xinhua) -- Austria did not have problem
in confidence when they face powerhouse Italy on Tuesday, coach
Herbert Prohaska said on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
"Austria's problem obviously has nothing to do with confidence
since we have equalized during injury twice. In defence, we played
calmly, without making too many mistakes in placing the ball and
relaunching play," said Prohaska in Margaux near Bordeaux.
</P>
<P>
Prohaska believed his strikers would have a mountain to climb
facing a Italian defence that features Paolo Maldini, Alessandro
Nesta, Fabio Cannavaro and Alessandro Costacurta.
</P>
<P>
He added, "We'll probably see some one-on-one situations with
Roberto Baggio and Alessandro Del Piero."
</P>
<P>
However, Prohaska pointed out the Italians may face more pressure
than his squad do in their last group B match in the new Stade de
France in St. Denis outside Paris.
</P>
<P>
"If Austria loses, it won't be the end of the world, but it would
be for Italy. If Italy doesn't run away with the game, Austria could
be all right, so long as my team doesn't make any mistakes." 
</P>
</TEXT>
