<HEADLINE> Stoichkov Says Jersey-throwing "Friendly" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 21 (Xinhua) -- Bulgarian striker Hristo Stoichkov said
on Sunday his gesture of throwing his jersey on Michel Platini at
break of a game on Friday was "totally friendly".
</P>
<P>
Stoichkov had thrown her No. 8 jersey to the French World Cup
Organizing Committee president on his way to locker room but the
latter received with a smile.
</P>
<P>
"I would never have offered my jersey to someone for whom I didn't
have deep respect. It was truly a friendly gesture," he said.
</P>
<P>
"I was very annoyed to read in a French paper that it was
interpreted as an act of definance towards Michel Platini. He and I
are friends," he said. 
</P>
