<HEADLINE> Syrian President Meets EU Envoy on Peace Process </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAMASCUS, June 21 (Xinhua) -- Syrian President Hafez al-Assad
Sunday held talks with European Union's Mideast peace envoy Miguel
Angel Moratinos on the stalled Middle East peace process and
efforts exerted to break the current impasse.
</P>
<P>
Emerging from the talks, Moratinos told reporters that he and
al-Assad discussed the latest developments in the peace process
and the deadlock in the process due to the intransigent policies
of the Israeli government.
</P>
<P>
Moratinos stressed that the EU attaches great importance to the
Mideast peace process, underlining the importance of continuing
the peace process on the basis of Madrid principles.
</P>
<P>
He said al-Assad expressed the hope that Europe would play a
more active role in the peace process.
</P>
<P>
The EU, in a final statement of its summit in Cardiff, Britain,
early this week, called for the Israeli recognition of
Palestinians' right to self-determination.
</P>
<P>
The EU envoy arrived here Saturday morning for a visit to Syria
as part of his tour in the Middle East to consult with leaders of
the region on the peace process.
</P>
<P>
He held talks with Syrian Foreign Minister Farouq al-Sharaa on
Saturday and discussed some EU ideas on the resumption of the
peace talks on the Syrian and Lebanese tracks.
</P>
<P>
They also discussed the French-Egyptian proposal on holding an
international conference to push forward the peace process and
underlined the importance of proper arrangement for any meeting in
this regard. 
</P>
