<HEADLINE> Lebanese FM Accuses Israel of Conducting Beirut </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, June 21 (Xinhua) -- Lebanese Foreign Minister Fares
Boueiz Sunday accused Israel of conducting the explosion near the
U.S. embassy in Beirut in the day.
</P>
<P>
The Voice of the People radio quoted Boueiz as saying that the
explosion took place when the Israeli government is taking
hard-line policy in the peace process and refusing to make any
compromises.
</P>
<P>
Israel is trying to divert people's attention from its stance
on the Mideast peace process through undermining Lebanese
stability, he added.
</P>
<P>
At noon Sunday, three rocket-propelled grenades exploded about
500 meters away from the U.S. embassy in Beirut, causing no human
and material losses.
</P>
<P>
Lebanese security forces have found part of the timing device on
the scene and launched investigation.
</P>
<P>
This is the second explosion in less than a week which took
place in the capital. Three days ago, a booby-trapped bomb in a
car exploded in a commercial area in downtown Beirut, killing the
driver and a passer-by.
</P>
<P>
Diplomats here said these explosions are aimed at undermining
the stability of Lebanon which is recovering from the damages in
the 1975-1990 civil war and seeking to give the world an image of
security. 
</P>
