<HEADLINE> Egypt Rejects Israeli Jerusalem Plan as </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, June 21 (Xinhua) -- Egyptian Foreign Minister Amr Moussa
Sunday rejected as illegitimate the Israeli plan to extend
Jerusalem municipal authority over eight Jewish settlement in the
West Bank.
</P>
<P>
The plan would only lead to instability of the city and change
its status which should be defined through negotiations on a final
agreement between the Palestinians and Israel, Moussa told
reporters.
</P>
<P>
After a five-hour debate, the Israeli cabinet Sunday approved a
controversial plan on extending the Jerusalem municipal authority
over eight West Bank Jewish settlements surrounding Jerusalem to
the east, north and south.
</P>
<P>
The Palestinian National Authority has denounced the plan as a
new attempt to destroy the peace process. It accused the Israeli
move of violating the signed agreements, which call on the two
sides to refrain from unilateral actions concerning the city.
</P>
<P>
"The plan is another provocation to both the Arab and Islamic
world as well as the international community," Moussa said, urging
the Israeli government to reconsider its policy which constitutes
another encroachment on the peace process.
</P>
<P>
Israel captured the traditionally Arab East Jerusalem in the
1967 Mideast War. The Palestinians want it as the capital of their
future independent state.
</P>
<P>
The Palestinian-Israeli peace talks have been deadlocked since
March 1997 when Israel began construction of a Jewish settlement in
East Jerusalem. 
</P>
