<HEADLINE> CPC Committee to Oversee Financial Sector </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 22 (Xinhua) -- The Central Committee of the
Communist Party of China (CPC) has established a special
work committee to oversee the country's crucial financial sector.
</P>
<P>
A recent Beijing conference to mark the establishment of the
CPC Central Committee Financial Work Committee was attended by
leading Party officials in major banking institutions
headquartered in the Chinese Capital.
</P>
<P>
Vice-Premier Wen Jiabao, secretary of the work committee, told
participants that the establishment of the group represents an
important decision the Party leadership made to strengthen Party
building in the financial sector, deepen financial reform, and
perfect a modern financial system in China.
</P>
<P>
The work committee will be responsible for ensuring the safe,
efficient, stable and healthy operation of the financial industry,
said Wen, who is also a member of the CPC Central Committee's
political bureau and Secretariat.
</P>
<P>
Wen noted that the committee will lead, ensure, control,
supervise and coordinate financial issues.
</P>
<P>
He said the committee will adhere to the principle of the
separation of functions of the Party, government and
enterprises. It will not interfere normal financial operations
while trying to ensure implementation of the Party line,
principles and policies for the industry.
</P>
<P>
Wen added that the CPC Central Committee has also set up a
disciplinary work committee for the financial sector. 
</P>
</TEXT>
