<HEADLINE> Sampras, Agassi Win in Straight Sets </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 22 (Xinhua) -- Americans Pete Sampras and Andre
Agassi both sailed into the second round at the Wimbledon Open
tennis tournament on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The top-seeded Sampras opened play on Center Court with a 6-3,
6-3, 6-2 victory over Slovakia's Dominik Hrbraty.
</P>
<P>
Within seconds of Sampras winning his match, 1992 champion
Agassi completed a 6-2, 6-4, 6-3 victory on Court 1 over Spain's
Alex Calatrava.
</P>
<P>
The tournament suffered a major blow when 17-year-old Russian
star Anna Kournikova withdrew with torn ligaments in her right
thumb.
</P>
<P>
In an early match, third-seeded Petr Korda, the Australian Open
champion, needed less than 90 minutes to defeat Spain's Javier
Sanchez, 6-3, 6-4, 6-3.
</P>
<P>
The highest women's seed in action Monday, No. 2 Lindsay
Davenport of the United States, cruised to a 6-2, 6-2 victory in
50 minutes over Argentina's Florencia Labat.
</P>
<P>
The first women's seed to advance was No. 9 Amanda Coetzer of
South Africa, who beat Kerry-Anne Guse of Australia 6-2, 6-2 in
just over an hour. 
</P>
</TEXT>
