<HEADLINE> 33 Tamil Rebels Killed, 100 Injured in Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, June 22 (Xinhua) -- Thirty-three Tamil rebels were
killed and more than 100 others injured Monday in fierce fighting
in East Sri Lanka between the rebels and government troops,
according to a military spokesman here.
</P>
<P>
Spokesman Irk Dewage said the troops Monday engaged in
operation to capture Vakarai in Batticaloa district in Eastern
Province.
</P>
<P>
Vakarai has been used by the rebels as one of their major bases
in the province and the rebels put up resistance initially but
then fled the area. Prior to fleeing the area, the rebels had
destroyed the Vakarai Hospital and a few other buildings in the
area, he said.
</P>
<P>
One soldier was also killed in action and four others were
injured.
</P>
<P>
A main base at Vakarai and a number of small rebel camps in the
area were demolished by the troops, who also destroyed a port
maintained by the rebels at Vakarai for boat movement.
</P>
<P>
Capture of Vakarai area by the troops will hinder the sea
movement of the rebels between the north and the east, the
spokesman said, adding that successful operation was carried out
by the army, the navy and the air force jointly.
</P>
<P>
The Tamil rebels have been fighting a war against the
government for a separate state in the north and east of the
country since 1983. 
</P>
</TEXT>
