<HEADLINE> Italy Try to Finish Top of Group B </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
PARIS, June 22 (Xinhua) -- Italy will try to finish top of Group
B by beating Austria in a match at Saint-Denis on Tuesday to avoid
Brazil in the second round of World Cup finals.
</P>
<P>
To do this, the Italian team should show the killer instinct in
the crucial match.
</P>
<P>
The deciding factor will be whether Italy's attack led by
Christian Vieri gets the support from the rest of the team.
</P>
<P>
Italian coach Cesare Maldini had critised the team's midfield,
which instead of moving forwards, has gone into reverse gear.
</P>
<P>
Maldini said:"We have to keep getting better. If we don't,
we'll be going home."
</P>
<P>
If the forwards get the support they need, then the Italian team
will be stronger than they appeared in their first two matches.
</P>
<P>
Vieri said:"I'm a striker and scoring goals is my job. And one
thing is for sure, I'm not stopping at three goals. I've got to
make the most of being on form."
</P>
<P>
The Italian coach knows that Austrians will not give up their
fight though they have not beaten Italy since 1960.
</P>
<P>
Austria have twice earned a 1-1 draw in the closing seconds
earlier in the World Cup finals.
</P>
<P>
Autraian coach Herbert Prohaska said:"I don't think the record
counts for very much. But if Austria were to win, it would go down
in our history, like the time we beat West Germany in the 1978 World
Cup in Argentina."
</P>
<P>
"We made a lot of mistakes against Chile and Cameroon. But we
worked hard and kept running, and were able to sort things out in
the end." said Prohaska.
</P>
<P>
The match between Italy and Austria will see if the Austrians
can sort things out a third time at the World Cup. 
</P>
</TEXT>
