<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 1430 GMT, June 22 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Israel's newly adopted Jerusalem expansion plan
drew wide criticism inside and outside the Jewish state.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli cabinet Sunday approved a plan to extend Jerusalem
municipal authority over eight settlements in the West Bank, which
is seen as steps to unilaterally expand Jerusalem's borders.
</P>
<P>
In its Monday editorial, Israel's influential newspaper
Ha'aretz said "the plan almost certainly is intented to create
territorial continuity between Jerusalem and the Jewish cities and
settlements -- such as Ma'aleh Adumim and Givat Ze'eve -- that
today are the very heart of Palestinian territory."
(Israel-Jerusalem Expansion-Criticism)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
KUCHING -- The meeting of ministers responsible for trade of
Asia-Pacific Economic Cooperation (APEC) opened here Monday
afternoon with a call for APEC to support initiatives to deal with
the financial crisis in the region. (Malaysia-APEC-Meeting)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
TOKYO -- Japan on Monday handed supervisory power over the
nation's financial industry to a new watchdog agency to make
financial administration more transparent.
</P>
<P>
The new Financial Supervision Agency was set up under the
Japanese Prime Minister's Office following the series of bribery
scandals involving Finance Ministry officials.
</P>
<P>
It will carry out inspections of banks, brokerage houses and
insurance firms, and is entitled to impose administrative
punishments on financial institutions. (Japan-Finance-Supervision)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
