<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, June 22 (Xinhua) -- The Karachi Stock Exchange
(KSE)-100 Index went down Monday by 8.58 points to close at
1,007.48 against Last Friday's close of 1,016.06 points.
</P>
<P>
A total volume of 46.7 million shares was traded Monday against
57.5 million shares traded last Friday.
</P>
<P>
There were 55 gainers and 71 losers while 56 scrips remained
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
The Karachi shares were down Monday as traders reacted to the
lows in the Indian markets and many held their positions waiting
for incentives in the government trade policy to be announced
later in the evening.
</P>
<P>
Traders say the trends in the Indian markets Monday made them
react and trading volumes remained low at the Karachi bourse as a
result.
</P>
<P>
Others were waiting for the government to unveil its annual
trade policy later Monday. Commerce Minister Ishaq Dar is expected
to announce an ambitious trade policy for the 1998-99 fiscal year
(July 1 -June 30) which plans to increase exports by more than 20
percent in the new fiscal year.
</P>
<P>
And traders at the Karachi bourse were holding their positions
to see the incentives the government plans to offer in this
regard.
</P>
<P>
Analysts predict that the Karachi bourse will rise on Tuesday
in reaction to the new trade policy to be announced late Monday
evening.  
