Agency (KCNA), the spokesman noted that the North Atlantic Treaty
Organization (NATO) has mounted military pressures onto Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
On June 15, NATO sent some 80 warplanes to areas around Kosovo,
a Yugoslav province, on an air strike exercise, so as to press
Belgrade for resuming talks with breakaway ethnic Albanians there.
</P>
<P>
"NATO's attempt at such armed intervention is exacerbating the
Kosovo crisis and gravely threatening the sovereignty and
territorial integrity of Yugoslavia," said the spokesman. 
</P>
