IMF funds, Summers said the IMF made the decision by itself.
</P>
<P>
The IMF promised last October to provide 10 billion U.S.
dollars of the 43 billion dollar fund which the agency brokered to
bail out Indonesia's ailing economy.
</P>
<P>
Indonesia received the first tranche of 3 billion dollars from
the IMF in November last year, but the second disbursement of 3
billion dollars scheduled for June was delayed due to riots in
Jakarta in May and the political crisis in the country which
forced former President Soeharto to step down.
</P>
<P>
The IMF executive board is expected to meet late this month to
discuss the timetable for the disbursement of loans to Indonesia.
 
