<HEADLINE> Sudanese Flee to Chad as Crisis Escalates </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, June 22 (Xinhua) -- Escalating ethnic strife over
land rights in Sudan's western Darfur State has sent more than
6,000 Sudanese fleeing into neighboring Chad, the independent
East African weekly reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
Darfur Governor Ibrahim Yaha Abdul Rahman was quoted as saying
that the conflict between Arabs in the area and the black Fur
community has left 235 dead, 43 injured and some 74 villages
ablaze.
</P>
<P>
