forces may be behind the conflict, noting that sophisticated
weapons had been used by both sides.
</P>
<P>
Unconfirmed reports said that the Arabs in Darfur were armed
by the Muslim-dominated Khartoum government to help fight the
rebel Sudan People's Liberation Army (SPLA), while the Fur and
other African groups are obtaining arms from civilians in
neighboring Chad. 
