<HEADLINE> North China Province Investing in Major Infrastructure Projects </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, June 22 (Xinhua) -- North China's Liaoning Province
will invest more than 97.6 billion yuan on 23 major infrastructure
projects this year.
</P>
<P>
A provincial official said these infrastructure projects
include construction in such areas as transportation, water
conservation, power plants, and telecommunication networks.
</P>
<P>
With an investment of 9.24 billion yuan, the 360-kilometer
Shenyang-Shanhaiguan expressway is under construction. The
Shenyang-Siping expressway, 161 kilometers long with an investment
of 2.39 billion yuan, should begin operations in August.
</P>
<P>
As the country's key project during the 1996-2000 period,
electrification of the Harbin-Dalian railway will be completed
within two years. The 946-kilometer line is expected to cost 5.25
billion yuan. Construction on the line began in 1993.
</P>
<P>
Liaoning Province also is expanding its telecommunication
networks. About 7.3 billion yuan will be used this year to ensure
an increase of 630,000 lines on the telephone switchboard within
the province. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
