<HEADLINE> HK Stocks Close Sharply Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 22 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong stocks suffered a
heavy setback Monday with the key Hang Seng Index slumping 387.70
points, or 4.51 percent, to close at 8,204.21.
</P>
<P>
Continued worries over ailing Japanese economy and its banking
problems prompted investors to take profit following an 8.5
percent gain in the Hang Seng Index last week.
</P>
<P>
The market dropped 60.61 points, or 0.71 percent, to open at
8,531.30, and shed 105.50 points, or 1.23 percent, to close the
morning session at 8,486.41.
</P>
<P>
Property stocks were the hardest hit among the blue chips, with
the Hang Seng properties sub-index dropping 7.06 percent to
9,213.46 points. The other three sectors suffered a loss of 3-4
percent.
</P>
<P>
In China plays, the red chip index slid 93.39 points, or
8.85 percent, to 961.79 points and the H-share index tumbled
30.02 points, or 6.18 percent, to 455.64.
</P>
<P>
Turnover was moderate at 5,650 million HK dollars (724 million
U.S. dollars).  
</P>
</TEXT>
