<HEADLINE> Commemorative Cards Issued to Mark 1st Anniversary of HK Return </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 22 (Xinhua) -- The Agricultural Bank of China
(ABC), one of the country's four big state-owned commercial banks,
today issued commemorative cards to mark the first anniversary of
the return of Hong Kong on July 1 of last year.
</P>
<P>
Altogether 199,871 sets of what are called Golden Spike
Commemorative Cards are to be issued, and each of them includes
five pieces with a combined face value of 1,900 yuan and is issued
at 1,998 yuan.
</P>
<P>
The cards can be circulated at the bank's designated commercial
entities within one year after they are issued, according to a bank
official.
</P>
<P>
ABC issued its first golden spike card in 1991 and the total
number of such cards issued since then has exceeded 10 million.
The cards are accepted by more than 40,000 agents and 70,000
commercial businesses across China.
</P>
<P>
The official said that ABC also plans to issue international
cards in the second half of this year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
