<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, June 22 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Kuala
Lumpur Stock Exchange closed lower Monday after a relatively quiet
session, undermined by the weak local currency ringgit which
tracked the Japanese yen's movement.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the 100-quality stock Composite Index lost 10.00
points to end at 457.61, the all-share Emas Index shed 1.91 points
to 117.79, the Industrial Index lost 3.12 points to 906.39 and the
Second Board Index dropped 2.42 points to 101.21.
</P>
<P>
The day's turnover stood at 75.365 million shares valued at
164.035 million ringgit (41.633 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
On the Main Board, turnover fell to 71.473 million shares
valued at 157.449 million ringgit (39.961 million dollars) from
108.738 million shares valued at 231.458 million ringgit (58.745
million dollars) traded last Friday.
</P>
<P>
Turnover on the Second Board dropped to 3.892 million shares
valued at 6.585 million ringgit (1.671 million dollars) from last
Friday's 3.946 million shares valued at 6.012 million ringgit
(1.525 million dollars).
</P>
<P>
Off-market deals rose to 3.687 million shares valued at 14.215
million ringgit (3.607 million dollars) from 1.174 million shares
valued at 3.888 million ringgit (0.986 million dollars) last
Friday.
</P>
<P>
On a sectoral basis, consumer products accounted for 6.150
million shares traded on the main board, industrial products 6.206
million shares, construction 6.352 million shares, trade/services
26.573 million shares, infrastructures 211,000 shares, finance
11.017 million shares, hotels 83,000 shares, properties 7.709
million shares, plantation 2.742 million shares, mining 156,200
shares, trusts 116,000 shares, closed/fund 21,000 shares and loans
4.138 million shares. 
</P>
