<HEADLINE> Iran Celebrates Soccer Victory over U.S. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, June 22 (Xinhua) -- Soon after the Iranian soccer team
beat the U.S. team in Lyon, France, 2-1, crowds of Tehran citizens
rushed to streets to celebrate the ground-breaking World Cup
victory.
</P>
<P>
The joyful people, particularly the young soccer fans, drove
cars, motorcycles with light on, beeping and sounding their horns
along streets, wavering Iranian flags and shouting "Iran, Iran."
</P>
<P>
Expressing their joy and cheers, the Iranian people gathered at
different squares and streets for hours after the Iran-U.S. match
in Lyon.
</P>
<P>
Top Iranian leaders, including the supreme leader Ayatollah Ali
Khamenei, President Mohammad Khatami and Majlis Speaker Nateq
Nouri, released separate congratulation messages, lauding the
victory over the U.S.
</P>
<P>
Iranian supreme leader Ayatollah Ali Khamenei said in his
message that the "courageous and fair play" of the Iranian players
was a beautiful image of Iranian nation's endeavors in every field
of their revolutionary life.
</P>
<P>
Iranian President Mohammad Khatami said in his message that he
shared the happiness of millions of Iranians on the victory of the
courageous and diligent Iranian footballers.
</P>
<P>
He stressed the importance of perseverance, endeavor, unity
coupled with art and thought in whatever field of activity,
including sports like soccer or wrestling.  
</P>
</TEXT>
