<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Macao Announces New Measures to Encourage Export </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, June 22 (Xinhua) -- Macao Government announced Monday to
reduce the fee for the identification of Macao-made goods to
encourage export.
</P>
<P>
The announcement, which was published on Monday's Government
Bulletin, said the identification fee for export-oriented goods
under the quota system will be cut from current 0.7 percent to 0.5
percent.
</P>
<P>
The new measure is aimed at lessening the costs of export so as
to improve the competitiveness of Macao-made products, said the
announcement.
</P>
<P>
In addition, a subsequent reform will be conducted on the
current foreign export procedures. The reform is also meant to
improve the competitiveness of Macao goods by introducing the
electronic data exchange system.
</P>
<P>
Macao's export value in the first four months of this year
declined by six percent from the same period last year, to have
reached 4.394 billion patacas (about 549.25 million US dollars) as
a result of the financial turmoil in Asia.
</P>
<P>
Garments and textiles made up 81 percent of all exports in
Macao, which were mainly shipped to the United States and European
Union.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
