<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Bank Increases Loans for Housing Sector </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 22 (Xinhua) -- The Bank of China, one of China's
big-four state-owned commercial banks, will increase its financial
support for the country's housing sector, according to an official
agreement signed today.
</P>
<P>
BOC will increase its proportion of loans for the real estate
sector by two percentage points each year, raising the rate to
eight percent from the current 3.7 percent, said the agreement
signed between the bank and the Ministry of Construction.
</P>
<P>
The proportional increase means that BOC's outstanding loans
for the real estate sector will rise from 20 billion yuan to 56
billion yuan in the years to come.
</P>
<P>
To achieve the goals, BOC will expand its yuan lending for
ordinary residential housing construction and increase
policy-oriented financial support for the real estate sector. It
will also experiment with business in foreign exchange loans and
mortgage.
</P>
<P>
BOC, China's major foreign exchange bank, budgeted 11 billion
yuan in loans for housing construction and consumption this
year. The figure is 18 percent of the bank's increased loans in
1998, according to a bank official.
</P>
<P>
He said that lending priority will be given to ordinary
residential housing construction and to real estate projects now
under construction.
</P>
<P>
BOC is considering to increase its variety of real-estate loans
and launch combined loaning programs involving both the local
currency and foreign exchange, the official said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
