<HEADLINE> BOC Extends Huge Loans for Beijing's Urban Construction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 22 (Xinhua) -- The Bank of China (BOC) today
signed an agreement with the Beijing Municipal Government to
provide three billion yuan in loans for the capital's
infrastructure projects.
</P>
<P>
The lending is part of the bank's financial support package for
Beijing's construction of infrastructure and basic projects.
According to a letter of intent the bank and the municipal government
signed today, the bank will extend a total of seven billion yuan
in loans for Beijing's major projects and enterprise groups.
</P>
<P>
A bank official said today that BOC will also sign similar
lending programs with the provinces of Jiangsu, Shaanxi, Henan and
Fujian and Shanghai Municipality.
</P>
<P>
The planned lendings are intended to assist the restructuring
effort of the state-owned enterprises and help boost economic
growth in the respective areas, he said.
</P>
<P>
Official data indicate that the BOC Beijing Branch now has 21
billion yuan and 1.55 billion US dollars of outstanding loans to
Beijing Municipality.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, BOC has raised buyer's credits and mixed government
loans from Britain, France, Canada, Italy and Japan to aid
Beijing's effort to build up its sectors of posts and
telecommunications, public transportation, energy, urban
facilities, and raw materials. 
</P>
</TEXT>
