<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU Mideast Envoy to Visit Egypt Thursday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, June 22 (Xinhua) -- European Union (EU) Special Envoy to
the Middle East Miguel Angel Moratinos will start a visit to Egypt
Thursday in new efforts to revive the stalled Mideast peace
process.
</P>
<P>
The visit comes out of the EU's keenness on activating the
peace process on the basis of the agreements signed between the
Palestinians and Israelis, the Madrid conference, and the Oslo
Agreement, Egypt's Middle East News Agency quoted British
diplomats here as saying.
</P>
<P>
During his two-day visit, Moratinos will hold talks with
Secretary General of the Arab League Esmat Abdel-Meguid, Egyptian
Foreign Minister Amr Moussa and senior Egyptian officials on the
long-running deadlock in the Mideast peace-making.
</P>
<P>
He will also brief Egyptian officials on the outcome of his
recent talks in Damascus, Tel Aviv and Beirut during his current
regional tour on reviving the peace talks.
</P>
<P>
The peace talks between Israel on one side and Syria and
Lebanon on the other have been stalled for more than two years due
to Israel's hardline policy.
</P>
<P>
Netanyahu refused to hand back to Syria the strategic Golan
Heights which Israel captured in the 1967 Middle East and proposed
to withdraw from the occupied south Lebanon on conditional basis.
</P>
<P>
During his visit, Moratinos will present fresh ideas to
Lebanese leaders in a bid to revive the peace talks in the
Lebanese and Syrian tracks in the peace process. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
