<DOCNO> XIE19980622.0154 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Two South African Players Expelled from World Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
PARIS, June 22 (Xinhua) -- Two players from South African team
Brendan Augustine and Naughty Mokoena will be sent home on Monday
for staying out late at a Night club, the South African team
officials announced.
</P>
<P>
The two players visited a Vichy night club on Saturday night and
returned after curfew in the early hours of Sunday morning.
</P>
<P>
The South African Football Association (SAFA) announced that the
two players would be suspended for the rest of the World Cup.
</P>
<P>
"The players defied us by staying out until five o'clock in the
morning. One of our security officials tried to stop them but they
defied him." said SAFA president Molefi Oliphant.
</P>
<P>
SAFA chief executve officer Danny Jordaan said:"They said they
made a mistake but it was defiance. We are determined and serious
about our World Cup campaign. We have to ensure a platform from
which the players can perform."
</P>
<P>
It was the second time that South African players broke curfew
in a camp. Five players were caught at a Vichy night club ahead of
the team's first game against France last week and forced to
apologise to the coach. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
