<HEADLINE> Batistuta Aims at Golden Boot Award </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
PARIS, June 22 (Xinhua) -- Argentine Striker Gabriel Batistuta,
who scored the first hat-trick so far at the France'98 World Cup
finals, said he wanted the Golden Boot award.
</P>
<P>
It was Batistuta's second hat-trick in two successive World Cup
finals. In 1994, he produced the feat in the match against the
United States.
</P>
<P>
Batistuta now leads the scorers' list with four goals.
</P>
