<HEADLINE> Insurance Industry Develops Rapidly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 22 (Xinhua) -- China had 25 insurance companies
in operation by the end of 1997, including 13 domestic and seven
overseas operations.
</P>
<P>
The companies employed a total of 350,000 people, including
over 140,000 people working for 7,460 branches of Chinese
insurance firms.
</P>
<P>
A total of 106 overseas insurers from 15 foreign countries and
regions had opened 189 representative offices in China by the end
of last year.
</P>
<P>
The figures were announced at the ongoing industry symposium --
China's Insurance Industry: Comparison and Choices -- in
Shanghai. Experts from China and the United States are attending
the meeting.
</P>
<P>
Official figures for 1997 show that China's insurance premiums
totaled 108.74 billion yuan, with domestic insurance companies
recording a 39.19 percentage points increase in earnings to 108.1
billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The World Bank estimates that total premiums for the country's
insurance industry will hit 250 billion yuan by the end of the
century. 
</P>
</TEXT>
