<HEADLINE> Strong Quake Rocks Southwestern Japan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, June 22 (Xinhua) -- A Strong earthquake measuring 5.1 on the
open-ended Richter scale jolted the Amami group of islands in
Kagoshima Prefecture, southwestern Japan, on Monday afternoon, the
Meteorological Agency said.
</P>
<P>
There were no immediate reports of damage or casualties, and no
tidal waves warning was issued.
</P>
<P>
The quake, which occurred at 4:07 p.m. (local time), was centered
about 60 kilometers under the sea off Amami-Oshima Island, southwest
of Kyushu, the agency said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
