<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai's Per-Capita GDP Keeps Rapid Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 22 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai's per-capita gross
domestic product (GDP) has maintained a rapid growth rate since
1992, which has also promoted the development of the surrounding
regions.
</P>
<P>
The latest figures from the Shanghai Statistics Bureau indicate
that the per-capita GDP of Shanghai reached 25,750 yuan (3,100 US
dollars) in 1997, increasing by 12.4 percent from the same period
last year, to rank first in the country.
</P>
<P>
Statistics also show that the municipality's per-capita GDP has
grown four times as much as that of the country's average level
during the last five years.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai's adjacent cities such as Suzhou and Wuxi also have
benefited from its rapid economic growth, according to the
statistics.
</P>
<P>
The per capita GDP of Wuxi, for instance, reached 20,000 yuan
(2,410 US dollars) in 1996.  
</P>
</TEXT>
