<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kampala Mayor Likely to Face Imprisonment in U.S. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, June 22 (Xinhua) -- The mayor of Uganda's capital
Kampala, who was detained in the United States for false
statements to Customs officers and illicit financial
transactions, is likely to face a prison term in the foreign
country.
</P>
<P>
Nasser Sebaggala was arrested by Customs agents at John F.
Kennedy Airport on June 13 as he prepared to board a Sabena
Airways flight from New York to Brussels en route to Kampala.
</P>
<P>
He had been attending an international conference on garbage
collection in Chicago with his newly-wed wife Sarah Sebaggala.
</P>
<P>
He will appear in a U.S. court on Tuesday this week for making
false statements to Customs officers and being involved in check
fraud, the latest East African weekly reported.
</P>
<P>
The mayor reportedly ticked "NO" box in reply to a question
which required him to declare cash exceeding 10,000 U.S. Dollars
although he carried much more money than that.
</P>
<P>
He was also said to be involved in six counts of check fraud
totaling 191,000 Dollars.
</P>
<P>
Paul Reichler, the hired lawyer for embattled Sebaggala, said
his client would face a 35-year prison term and a fine of more
than one million Dollars if he was to be convicted on all the
charges.
</P>
<P>
While the lawyer demanded the mayor to be allowed to go back
to Kampala, Amy Rindskopf, a spokeswoman for the U.S. Attorney's
office in Boston, said she strongly doubted that possibility
before his trial.
</P>
<P>
Ugandans' response to the mayor's arrest has been clearly
reflected in the behaviors of his rivals and supporters.
</P>
<P>
During his stay in the U.S., there is a resurfacing of a
strong demand for his stepping down because he was not
academically qualified to host the top post in the capital.
</P>
<P>
He is said not to have the required Advanced Level certificate
or its equivalent. Meanwhile, his supporters have tried to raise
money for his bail. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
