<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980622.0199 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Confident of Economic Growth Target, Top Official Says </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 22 (Xinhua) -- China has full confidence in
attaining its economic growth target of 8 percent this year,
Chinese Minister of Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation
(MOFTEC) Shi Guangsheng said here today.
</P>
<P>
His remarks came when answering a question at a news
conference sponsored by the Information Office of the State
Council of China.
</P>
<P>
He said that the first quarter of this year reflected sound
economic development in China with an increase of 7.2 percent in
its gross national product (GNP), a decrease of 1.5 percent in its
price index and an increase of 13.2 percent in its exports.
</P>
<P>
The achievements were made despite the difficulties brought
about by the Asian financial crisis, Shi said.
</P>
<P>
At the beginning of the year, he said, China clearly
acknowledged the negative influence the Asian financial crisis
would have on China's economic development, especially on exports
and foreign investment.
</P>
<P>
Because of this, China decided to take measures to ensure
the growth rate in its GNP, Shi said.
</P>
<P>
The measures included that China would increase domestic
input and expand domestic demand, he said. This year, China will
further increase its investment in the fields of agriculture,
environmental protection, energy, infrastructure and housing, Shi
said.
</P>
<P>
China will also tap the potential of rural markets by
encouraging the consumption of China's 800 million farmers, he
said.
</P>
<P>
China will also develop its foreign trade by expanding exports
and imports, as well as positively absorbing foreign investment.
</P>
<P>
He said that, although it is difficult for China to expand
exports while maintaining the value of its currency, China will
achieve stable growth in foreign trade by reducing cost,
optimizing the structure of exports and improving the investment
environment.
</P>
<P>
Shi said that the measures will soon prove productive and
effective.
</P>
<P>
He said China achieved an economic growth rate of 7.2 percent
in the first quarter of this year, when the measures had not been
put into effect. With these measures, he added, China will be sure
to achieve its GNP growth target. 
</P>
</TEXT>
