visit to China later this week will create favorable conditions
for the growth of Sino-U.S. economic and trade relations.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, according to Sun, such important topics as China's
entry into WTO will be discussed and agreements concerning some
important cooperative projects, like those on aeroplanes and power
stations, will be signed during his visit. He also expressed the
hope that U.S. government will abandon some economic sanctions
against China through President Clinton's visit.  
