<HEADLINE> Philippine Rebel Group Orders Arrest of Marcoses </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, June 22 (Xinhua) -- The leftist rebels New Peoples Army
(NPA) confirmed Monday that it had ordered the arrest of the kin
of the late president Ferdinand Marcos to protest the plan by
President-elect Joseph Estrada to bury Marcos at the heroes'
cemetery.
</P>
<P>
The main targets of the arrest are Imelda Marcos, widow of the
late president, and her son Ferdinand "Bonbong" Marcos Jr.,
newly-elected governor of Ilocos Norte, the Philippine News Agency
Monday quoted NPA spokesman Gregorio Rosal as saying.
</P>
<P>
Rosal said in a broadcast interview that the arrest order was
passed by the NPA's political wing, the Communist Party of the
Philippines.
</P>
<P>
Aside from the Marcoses, he said the cronies of the deposed
president will also be arrested.
</P>
<P>
He said administrations after the 1986 overthrow of Marcos,
headed by Corazon Aquino and incumbent President Fidel Ramos, had
"abandoned the quest for justice for thousands of victims of human
rights abuses under Marcos."
</P>
<P>
"But it appears the incoming Estrada regime will do worse than
the criminal negligence of the past two administrations," he said.
Estrada will take office on June 30 and he had decided to allow
the burial of Marcos' remains at the heroes' cemetery on July 11.
</P>
<P>
Defense Secretary Fortunato Abat, also in a broadcast
interview, belittled the threat and said the Marcoses can ask for
protection from the authorities. 
</P>
