<HEADLINE> Thailand's Chart Pattana Party Elects New Leader </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, June 22 (Xinhua) -- Chart Pattana Party, one of
Thailand's major political parties, elected a new leader in its
annual congress held here Monday.
</P>
<P>
Korn Dabbaransi was elected new party leader to replace the
late Chatichai Choonhavan, who died of cancer on May 6.
</P>
<P>
Korn, a nephew of Chatichai, has been deputy leader of the
party and was former deputy prime minister and industry minister
in the previous cabinet.
</P>
<P>
Chart Pattana Party, the third largest political party in
Thailand, holds 52 seats in the 293-strong National Assembly.
</P>
</TEXT>
