<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Zealand Stocks Finish Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Wellington, June 22 (Xinhua) -- The New Zealand share market
lost ground Monday on nervousness over weakness in overseas
markets.
</P>
<P>
The NZSE40 Index ended 33 points lower at 1,942 with a turnover
of 126 million dollars (65 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Among the leaders, Air New Zealand eased 2 cents to 186 cents.
Brierley Investment remained stable at 94 cents. Carter Holt
Harvey lost 14 cents to 160 cents. Fletcher Energy dived 21 cents
to 428 cents. Fletcher Building dropped 10 cents to 240 cents.
Telecom dipped 3 cents to 777 cents. Lion Nathan was the only main
leader to gain, up 3 cents to 428 cents.
</P>
<P>
Overall, there were 20 rises and 77 falls. 
</P>
</TEXT>
