<HEADLINE> Multinational Firms in North China Port City Are Profitable </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, June 22 (Xinhua) -- The majority of projects funded by
multinational companies in north China's largest port city have
already begun to make a profit and contribute to local economic
growth.
</P>
<P>
Tianjin has more than 300 overseas-funded enterprises invested
by some 200 multinational companies from more than 30 countries
and regions such as Japan, the United States, the Republic of
Korea (ROK), Britain, France, Germany and Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Local projects of multinational companies cover the areas of
electronics, food, machinery, automobiles, building materials,
light industry, chemicals, real estate and pharmaceuticals.
</P>
<P>
The company funded by Motorola in Tianjin leads the
overseas-funded projects in China with a total investment of 1.2
billion U.S. dollars. The U.S.-funded company also ranks the first
in Tianjin and second in China in terms of output value.
</P>
<P>
In addition, Motorola has set up joint ventures in other
provinces and cities in the country producing beepers, mobile
phones and multimedia computers.
</P>
<P>
More than 800 enterprises in 12 provinces in China provide
parts and components for Motorola, which also has over one billion
U.S. dollars of imports from the United States annually.
</P>
<P>
Tianjin has given priority to the effective use of investment
from multinational companies in an effort to further expand the
effort of opening up the economy.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
