<HEADLINE> U.S. Investors-Backed Firm Starts Chain Store, Retail Business </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, June 22 (Xinhua) -- Avon Products (Guangzhou) Ltd.,
a direct-sales company with financial backing from investors in
the United States, has announced plans to start a chain store and
retail business.
</P>
<P>
C. William Pryor, chairman of the board and president of Avon
Products (Guangzhou) Ltd., said last week that his company had
received permission from Guangzhou city's Administration for
Industry and Commerce to carry out the new operation plan.
</P>
<P>
As a supporting step, Avon products -- mainly cosmetics and
related commodities -- will be placed in stores. The existing
shops owned by Avon will be used for wholesale or retail sales.
</P>
<P>
While extending a warm welcome to its former business agents,
the Avon Products (Guangzhou) Ltd. leader also pledged to increase
investment for advertising.
</P>
<P>
Avon, which set up its first direct-sales subsidiaries in China
in 1990, currently has 75 subsidiaries in the country. It also has
established two manufacturing plants in Guangzhou City and Conghua
County, both in Guangdong Province.
</P>
<P>
China has banned all direct sales, citing them as a negative
element disturbing the economic order and affecting social
stability.
</P>
<P>
Foreign direct-sales enterprises were urged to engage in chain
store and retail businesses with proper approval, while domestic
ones should change to normal store management. Work on this aspect
will be completed by the end of October, according to a circular
by the State Council.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
