<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Guangzhou Set for Trade Fair </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, June 22 (Xinhua) -- The Sixth Guangzhou Economic and
Trade Fair will be held between July 15-20 in the capital city of
south China's Guangdong Province.
</P>
<P>
The first annual fair was held in 1993. The total trade volume
for the past five fairs approached 5.1 billion yuan, with the
events yielding contracts for 396 economic and technological
projects valued at 32.8 billion yuan, 2.3 billion US dollars of
which were from overseas.
</P>
<P>
The fair will feature exhibitions of new domestic and overseas
products and state-of-the-art technology, as well as investment
talks and lectures on technology.
</P>
<P>
The fair will focus on effort to transform Guangzhou into a
modern international metropolis, observers said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
