<HEADLINE> Thai Tycoons Out of Forbes Billionaire List </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, June 22 (Xinhua) -- Thailand has no more billionaires,
the Bangkok Post Monday quoted the U.S. magazine Forbes as saying.
</P>
<P>
Regional financial crisis had reduced the number of dollar
billionaires in Asia to 44 from 56, according to the magazine.
</P>
<P>
And Thailand's top tycoons were nowhere to be found, the
newspaper said.
</P>
<P>
According to the newspaper, Thailand had two entries last year:
Bangkok Bank's Chatri Sophonpanich at 2.2 billion U.S. dollars;
and the CP Group's Dhanin Chearavanont at 1.7 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
Back in 1996, 10 Thais led by Dhanin, whose wealth was reported
at 4.7 billion dollars, were included in the Forbes list.
</P>
<P>
Microsoft Chairman Bill Gates still topped this year's list of
the world's wealthiest people with his 51 billion dollars.
</P>
