<HEADLINE> Thailand Reduces Bus Services in Rainy Season </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, June 22 (Xinhua) -- Thailand is reducing its bus
services during the rainy season as the state-run Transport Co.
believes the rainy weather will dampen people's enthusiasm for
travel, the Bangkok Post said Monday.
</P>
<P>
The newspaper said the firm will cut the number of
inter-province buses during June and September by 20 percent.
</P>
<P>
The company said in the recent two months it suffered a drop in
income of some 40 percent.
</P>
<P>
The company was confronted with severe competition from private
buses in its inter-province routes.
</P>
<P>
The Thailand Development and Research Institute has suggested
that Transport Co. be split in two, with one running
inter-province buses, and the other an independent body
supervising service standards for the buses. 
</P>
