<HEADLINE> Vietnamese Deputy PM Visits Myanmar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, June 22 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Vietnamese Deputy Prime
Minister and Foreign Minister Nguyen Manh Cam is due to meet with
Myanmar Foreign Minister U Ohn Gyaw here Monday to exchange views
on regional and international issues, official newspaper The New
Light of Myanmar reported.
</P>
<P>
Nguyen arrived here Sunday evening at the invitation of U Ohn
Gyaw.
</P>
<P>
A meeting of the Myanmar-Vietnam Joint Commission for Bilateral
Cooperation (JCBC), which will be the third one, is also scheduled
to take place here later Monday to push ahead the two countries'
bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
A Vietnamese delegation led by Vice-Minister of Planning and
Investment Nguyen Xuan Thao, which arrived here last Wednesday,
will attend the Senior Officials' Meeting of the Third Meeting of
the Myanmar-Vietnam JCBC.
</P>
<P>
The delegation had held discussions with officials of the
Myanmar Foreign Ministry on a wide range of bilateral issues
including cooperation and matters of common interest, the report
said.
</P>
<P>
The Myanmar-Vietnam JCBC was established in May 1994 when
former Vietnamese Prime Minister Vo Van Kiet visited Myanmar. The
last JCBC meeting was held in Hanoi in January 1997, during which
measures to further promote multi-faceted cooperation,
particularly in trade, agriculture and forestry were discussed.
</P>
