<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shi Guangsheng: U.S. Becomes Largest Foreign Investor in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 22 (Xinhua)-- The United States has now become
the largest source of direct overseas investment in China, said
Shi Guangsheng, minister of foreign trade and economic
cooperation, here this morning.
</P>
<P>
From January to May, the actual U.S. investment in China had
exceeded 18 billion U.S. dollars, with a total of 24,000
enterprises registered here, Shi noted at a press conference
sponsored the Information Office of the State Council.
</P>
<P>
"U.S. companies here are comparatively more advanced in
technologies and have better management, with higher-quality
products, and thus they are widely welcome by the Chinese side,"
he added.
</P>
<P>
The minister predicts that U.S. President Bill Clinton's
visit to China later this week will create favorable
conditions for the growth of Sino-U.S. economic and trade
relations.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, according to Shi, such important topics as China's
entry into WTO will be discussed and agreements concerning some
important cooperative projects, like those on aeroplanes and power
stations, will be signed during his visit. He also expressed the
hope that U.S. government will abandon some economic sanctions
against China through President Clinton's visit.  
</P>
</TEXT>
