<HEADLINE> China Dominated Asian Junior Badminton Championships </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, June 21 (Xinhua) -- China captured three out of
five finals in the Asian Junior Badminton Championships which
ended here Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese players won the girls singles, girls doubles and
the mixed doubles titles.
</P>
<P>
However, Chinese Taipei's Chien Yu Hsiu was crowned the new
Asian Junior champion when he trashed Indonesia's third seed Endra
Ferianto 15-1, 15-1 in the boys singles final at the Kuala Lumpur
Badminton Stadium.
</P>
<P>
It was the 18-year-olds first win in a major junior tournament.
</P>
<P>
In an all Chinese affair, Hu Ting toppled her top seeded
teammate Gong Ruina 11-6, 11-6 in the girls singles final.
</P>
<P>
Gong partnered Huang Sui to defeat South Korea's Lee Hyo-jung
and Jun Woul Sihk 15-13, 15-8 in the girl's singles final.
</P>
<P>
Host Malaysia also had a podium finish when it won the boys
doubles final. Chan Chong Ming and Teo Kok Seng defeated China Guo
Siwei and Jiang Shan 15-7, 15-5.
</P>
<P>
However, Chan missed his opportunity for a double gold when he
and partner Joanne Quay lost to China's top seeds Jiang Shan and
Huang Sui 15-6, 8-15, 11-15 in the mixed doubles final. 
</P>
</TEXT>
