<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Garzelli Wins Swiss Tour Stage and Overall Lead </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, June 21 (Xinhua) -- Italy's Stefano Garzelli claimed
his second consecutive stage win and kept the overall lead in the
Tour of Switzerland around Lenzerheide of Switzerland on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Garzelli, made his first professional victory on Saturday,
surged ahead from a three-man sprint finish to the 156 km fifth
stage, crossing in front of compatriots Daniele De Paoli and
Leonardo Piepoli.
</P>
<P>
Italy's Davide Rebellin, who began the day clinging to a 10
seconds overall lead, watched his advantage eroded as Garzelli led
a three-man break on the final climb.
</P>
<P>
Garzelli gained a one minute 19 seconds lead over Piepoli and
Switzerland's Beat Zberg.
</P>
<P>
Most of Sunday's stage had been dominated by a brave solo break
by De Paoli, who went away after just 22 kms at the foot of the
first of four climbs.
</P>
<P>
The Italian held on grimly until five kms from the finish when
he was overtaken by Garzelli and Piepoli. 
</P>
</TEXT>
