<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Plays Important Role in Asia: Italian Newspaper </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, June 21 (Xinhua) -- U.S. President Bill Clinton is going
to China because China and its leaders are playing an increasingly
important role in Asia, a commentary in the Italian newspaper La
Republica said on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The commentary, entitled "Aim of Clinton's China Visit", said
the U.S. president's visit is due more to China's growing
prominence in Asia's political and economic prospects than to the
attraction offered by China's great market potentials.
</P>
<P>
China has exerted its utmost efforts to keep Asia's economic
stability during the financial crisis in the region and China's
currency RMB is playing a more and more important part as the
crisis persists, the commentary said.
</P>
<P>
It also noted the important position occupied by Chinese
President Jiang Zemin and Premier Zhu Rongji in Asia's political
scene, especially their key role amid the growing concerns over a
possible nuclear arms race after nuclear tests by India and
Pakistan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
