<HEADLINE> Pastrana Wins Colombian Presidential Election </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTAFE DE BOGOTA, June 21 (Xinhua) -- Opposition candidate
Andres Pastrana defeated ruling party candidate Horacio Serpa and
won Colombia's presidential run-off election, preliminary results
from the National Registry Office showed Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Of the 95 percent of votes counted, Pastrana took 51.1 percent,
against Serpa's 45.7 percent.
</P>
<P>
Serpa, representing the ruling Liberal Party, conceded defeat
later Sunday, calling for his fellow countrymen's support to the
president-elect. 
</P>
