<HEADLINE> Five Arrested for Drug Chemicals in Peru </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, June 21 (Xinhua) -- Peruvian Police had arrested five
suspects and confiscated 15 tonnes of drug chemicals in their
raids recently in the capital city Lima and other two northern
cities, police said Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The five suspects were believed to belong to a group that used
business in the capital and in Huarla and Huacho to sell the
supplies. The gang had set up a laboratory to process cocaine
paste in northern Lima.
</P>
<P>
The chemicals, items such as hydrochloric acid and sulphuric
acid, were hidden in company warehouses when they were discovered
by the police. 
</P>
