<HEADLINE> More Than 30,000 Hectares Burned in Florida Fires </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 21 (Xinhua) -- More than 30,000 hectares have
been burned in wildfires in drought-stricken counties of north and
central Florida since the beginning of June.
</P>
<P>
Firefighters had contained 70 percent of 5,280 hectares of
blazes in North Florida. But dry weather drives more new fires to
start each day. Local officials said 80 to 90 new fires were
expected daily unless Florida received some rainfall.
</P>
<P>
The fires this month have burned 30,870 hectares in 39
counties, damaging 72 homes and 41 other structures in Florida.
</P>
<P>
U.S. President Bill Clinton has declared the entire state a
fire disaster area. 
</P>
</TEXT>
