<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iran Scores First Win for Asia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LYON, France, June 21 (Xinhua) -- Iran became the first Asian
nation to win a game here after beating the United States 2-1 in group
F here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The United States campaign in these finals was finished after the
loss as they have been denied any chance for reaching the second stage
here.
</P>
<P>
Hamid Estili put Iran on the scoreboard in the 40th minute, when he
headed the ball home past keeper Kasey Keller on a pass from defender
Javad Zarincheh.
</P>
<P>
Iran was 2-0 ahead 36 minutes into the second half, when midfielder
Mehdi Mahdavikia made a lone run down the center and netted calmly in
the box.
</P>
<P>
The United States reduced the margin in the 87th minute on a header
from forward Brian McBride, who plays in the MLS league side Columbus
Crew.
</P>
<P>
Germany and Yugoslavia now tied at four points to lead the group
standings, followed by Iran at three. The United States were winless.
</P>
</TEXT>
