<HEADLINE> Jamaican Pleased with Team Performance Despite Defeat </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
PARIS, June 21 (Xinhua) -- Jamaican coach Rene Simoes said he
was pleased with his team's play despite the 5-0 defeat to the
Argentine team here on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
"I am pleased with my team and their play, if anyone can avoid
letting in fewer than four goals against a giant like Argentina,
they should consider themselves lucky." Simoes said.
</P>
<P>
"I decided to use a zonal defence instead of individual marking
because of the 'red card fever' prevalent over the last fre
matches," said Simoes, "But on the whole I am satisfied with the
refereeing."
</P>
<P>
One Jamaican player was sent off in the second half of the match.
</P>
<P>
Argentine midfielder Juan Veron said:"We played a very good
match againsta tough and physical side. I'd like to wish our coach
DAniel Alberto Passarella a happy fathers' Day. He is an essential
element in our victory."
</P>
<P>
Forward Claudio Lopez said:"We played a superb match, much
better than against Japan. We were able to move the ball forward
and take advantage of having lots of attacks."
</P>
<P>
Argentina now lead Group H with better goal difference than
Croatia, which have also collected 6 points from two wins. The two
teams will play their last group match to decide the group winners.
</P>
</TEXT>
